ng useful.<br><br>Bin Laden is not only responsible for Sept 11, he is responsible for the Cole bombing that killed 19, Bombings of embassies in Kenya and Tanzania in 1998 that killed over 200, and the 1993 WTC bombing.  He is likely also responsible for the recent Anthrax attacks in the US.<br><br>These are just the successful actions.  The CIA has reported that a number of other attempts have been thwarted, the ones they gave details of :<br><br>&quot;Among operations believed to have been thwarted: a planned attack on U.S. facilities in London early this year and an attack on FBI headquarters in Washington this past summer.&quot;<br><br>Now, 9 years after his first attack on the US, 9 years of sitting on our duffs being pacifists like you advocate, Bin Laden made a decisive victory against the US on US soil.  He destroyed the 2 tallest buildings on US soil, killed nearly 6000 people, and wrecked what was probably the most important financial center of the western world.<br><br>Frankly, world wars have been fought over far less than this.  It is not a question of attrition as you so mind numbingly state, it is a question of survivial.  It's only a matter of time before he does something really bad - as if this wasnt bad enough.<br><br>Picture it, 10 years from now, a half dozen other major terrorist actions in the US have come and gone, and a small nuke goes off in NYC.  Then another in Washington.  And another in LA, and one in Dalls.  That's a very real possibility.  <br><br>Or maybe it would be more gruesome and slow.  Maybe he manages to infect the water supply of a few blocks of NYC with Ebola.  If he hit the right areas, and several highly populated cities, he could kill millions just as if he had dropped an h-bomb.  <br><br>You think this is stupid?  Experience is a great teacher.  Hopefully Americans will not listen to people like you, so that just maybe we can eliminate this threat before it becomes far greater than it is now.<br><br>So,