n't going to be able to keep the farm and feed their family for long. Unlike the US, Afghanistan does not claim to be a democracy where the majority of citizens have a say in the actions of the government.<br><br>Got forwarded an interesting <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.smh.com.au/news/webdiary/2001/10/30/FFX4DIJJETC.html">article from the Sydney Morning Herald</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> today. Much of it is specific critisism of Australian involvement, but some people might find interesting bits there. Steps to prevent people mistaking unexploded cluster bomb munitions for food packages. University of Pittsberg students &quot;top 5 war lies&quot;. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.bangpound.org/afghanwirephotos/">Photos of casualties in Afghanistan</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. Questioning why the Pentagon has just employed a PR firm.<br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Why do the arguments and actions need any embellishment if they are so straightforward and undeniably right?<br><br>The obvious answer is because the arguments are not actually straightforward and undeniably right. In fact, the issues at stake in the war against terrorism are so complex, so debateable and so open to interpretation that it is probably beyond any of us to sum it all up in any meaningful way.<br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utrechdashadowknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trech Da ShadowKnight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 403<br> <font color=#E9D756>(10/30/01 6:59:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=214.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trech don't scare me like that</span><hr size=1> A citizenry is ultimately re